<Routines>
<Routine Name="Logic" Type="RLL">
<RLLContent>
<Rung Number="0" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[ARRAY_CTUD  REV 1.0

Array-based multi-channel up/down counter.
INT accumulator (0-32767). Up to 1050 independent channels.

INDEX MODES (Rungs 2-3):
  AUTO_INC = 0 (default): use CM_Inc -- you control the channel each scan
  AUTO_INC = 1          : AOI cycles INT_INC 0->1049->0 each scan
    Read <instance>.EFF_INC to know the active channel this scan.
    Example: XIC(CTU_ARRAY[MY_CTR.EFF_INC]) -> CTU input

CTU and CTD are EDGE-TRIGGERED (rising edge only).
One count per edge regardless of how long the bit is held.

C_CU / C_CD are one-scan-wide output pulses matching each count event.
Use them for diagnostics or to trigger downstream one-shot logic.

SIDE EFFECT: AOI clears the caller's RES bit after executing reset.
RESET_TO sets the reset value (default 0).

NOTE: Change CM_Inc/INT_INC only while CTU = 0 and CTD = 0.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[NOP();]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="1" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[LIMITATIONS AND HOW TO INCREASE THEM

--- CHANNEL COUNT (current: 1050, index 0-1049) ---
To increase:
  1. Increase Dimensions on all three arrays to the same new size:
       COUNT_ACC, CTU_ONS, CTD_ONS
  2. In Rung 4 change CMP(EFF_INC > 1049) to CMP(EFF_INC > <size-1>).
  3. In Rung 3 change MOD 1050 to MOD <new size>.

--- ACCUMULATOR / PRESET RANGE (current: INT, 0-32767) ---
To increase to DINT (0-2,147,483,647):
  Change PRE, RESET_TO, C_ACC params and COUNT_PRE, COUNT_ACC
  local tags from INT to DINT. Memory: 2 bytes/ch -> 4 bytes/ch.

--- AUTO MODE SWEEP TIME ---
In AUTO_INC=1 mode each channel is visited once every 1050 scans.
At a 10ms task, full sweep = ~10.5 seconds.

--- MEMORY vs STANDARD COUNTER TAGS ---
Standard COUNTER: 12 bytes each. 1050 tags = 12,600 bytes.
This AOI at 1050 channels (INT): ~3,400 bytes. ~9x smaller.

--- SCAN TIME ---
Each call is O(1). Add one call per active channel per scan.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[NOP();]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="2" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[INDEX RESOLUTION
  AUTO_INC = 0: EFF_INC = CM_Inc  (manual, you control the channel each scan)
  AUTO_INC = 1: EFF_INC = INT_INC (auto-cycle, AOI steps through 0-1049)
EFF_INC is Read Only -- read <instance>.EFF_INC from other rungs to know
which channel is active and index your own trigger/condition arrays.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[[XIO(AUTO_INC)CPT(EFF_INC,CM_Inc),XIC(AUTO_INC)CPT(EFF_INC,INT_INC)];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="3" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[AUTO-INCREMENT
When AUTO_INC = 1: advance INT_INC by 1 each scan, wrap at 1049.
Full sweep of all 1050 channels takes 1050 scans.
Note: if you increase the channel count, update the MOD value here to match.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIC(AUTO_INC)CPT(INT_INC,(INT_INC + 1) MOD 1050);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="4" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[FAULT CHECK
Suspend all indexed logic if EFF_INC is out of range.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[[CMP(EFF_INC < 0),CMP(EFF_INC > 1049)]OTE(CM_Fault);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="5" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[PRESET SYNC
Mirror scalar PRE into COUNT_PRE each scan.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[CMP(COUNT_PRE <> PRE)CPT(COUNT_PRE,PRE);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="6" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[RESET
On RES rising edge: reset ACC to RESET_TO, clear RES via OTU.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIO(CM_Fault)XIC(RES)CPT(COUNT_ACC[EFF_INC],RESET_TO)OTU(RES);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="7" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[COUNT UP  (edge-triggered)
ONS ensures exactly one increment per CTU rising edge.
Blocked when ACC >= COUNT_PRE.
C_CU fires one scan wide -- use for diagnostics or downstream one-shots.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIO(CM_Fault)CMP(COUNT_ACC[EFF_INC] < COUNT_PRE)XIC(CTU)ONS(CTU_ONS[EFF_INC])CPT(COUNT_ACC[EFF_INC],COUNT_ACC[EFF_INC] + 1)OTE(C_CU);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="8" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[COUNT DOWN  (edge-triggered)
ONS ensures exactly one decrement per CTD rising edge.
Blocked when ACC = 0.
C_CD fires one scan wide -- use for diagnostics or downstream one-shots.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIO(CM_Fault)CMP(COUNT_ACC[EFF_INC] > 0)XIC(CTD)ONS(CTD_ONS[EFF_INC])CPT(COUNT_ACC[EFF_INC],COUNT_ACC[EFF_INC] - 1)OTE(C_CD);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="9" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[DONE
C_DN fires when ACC = COUNT_PRE, or ACC = 0 with DN_0 set.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIO(CM_Fault)[CMP(COUNT_ACC[EFF_INC] = COUNT_PRE),CMP(COUNT_ACC[EFF_INC] = 0)XIC(DN_0)]OTE(C_DN);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="10" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[ACCUMULATOR OUTPUT
Mirror the active channel accumulator to scalar C_ACC.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIO(CM_Fault)CPT(C_ACC,COUNT_ACC[EFF_INC]);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
</RLLContent>
</Routine>
</Routines>
</AddOnInstructionDefinition>
</AddOnInstructionDefinitions>
</Controller>
</RSLogix5000Content>